{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, since we focus on closed-book QA, the practical implications from our study such as filtering-out Unknown fine-tuning examples still require validation in settings involving long-form text generation.",
    "To filter-out examples that introduce new factual knowledge in long-form gener-ation tasks, one would need to make adaptations to SliCK and come up with an effective way to compare the sampled answer with the ground-truth to approximate P Correct.",
    "We leave this for future work.",
    "Long-form generation tasks introduce evaluation challenges, leading to a wide adoption of LLM-based evaluations.",
    "Our choice to focus explicitly on closed book QA facilitates more accurate evaluation that enhances the reliability of our findings."
  ]
}